  "stat_block": {
    "bulk": {
      "subtype": "bulk",
      "text": "L",
      "type": "stat_block_section",
      "value": null
    },
    "craft_requirements": "You must be a mythic arcane spellcaster capable of supplying a casting of the spell at the listed rank.",
    "level": 4,
    "statistics": {
      "abilities": [
        {
          "ability_type": "offensive",
          "effect": "You Cast the Spell at the indicated rank. If you spend 1 Mythic Point as part of this activation, resolve the spell\u2019s effects at mythic proficiency.",
          "frequency": "once per day, plus overcharge",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "Cast a Spell",
              "aonid": 3521,
              "game-obj": "Actions",
              "name": "Cast a Spell",
              "type": "link"
            },
            {
              "alt": "Pathfinder Adventure Path #219: Lord of the Trinity Star pg. 70",
              "aonid": 283,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Pathfinder Adventure Path #219: Lord of the Trinity Star pg. 70",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Cast a Spell",
          "subtype": "ability",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        {
          "ability_type": "offensive",
          "action_type": {
            "name": "Reaction",
            "subtype": "action_type",
            "type": "stat_block_section"
          },
          "effect": "You disbelieve your failure, willing the check to success. Spend 1 Mythic Point and reroll the flat check, then resolve the spell\u2019s effects at mythic proficiency.",
          "frequency": "once per day",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "Pathfinder Adventure Path #219: Lord of the Trinity Star pg. 70",
              "aonid": 283,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Pathfinder Adventure Path #219: Lord of the Trinity Star pg. 70",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Reaction",
          "subtype": "ability",
          "trigger": "You fail the DC 10 flat check when you overcharge the wand",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        }
      ],
      "subtype": "statistics",
      "type": "stat_block_section",
      "usage": {
        "subtype": "usage",
        "text": "held in 1 hand",
        "type": "stat_block_section"
      }
    },
    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "Runelord Xanderghul often crafted *Cyrusian wands* to bolster his access to his favorite illusion spells. All *Cyrusian wands* look different but equally audacious in their coloration, shape, and glittering gemstone adornments.  \n  \nA *Cyrusian wand* only ever contains an arcane spell with the illusion trait.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 137,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "rare"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "e4b0e4f5f4b3d4cad3bea67ec077e297",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Rare",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This rarity indicates that a rules element is very difficult to find in the game world. A rare feat, spell, item or the like is available to players only if the GM decides to include it in the game, typically through discovery during play. Creatures with this trait are rare. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creatures is increased by 5.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 11,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "6a30ff50ed821ab5b9699b2f3d68c0d6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Arcane",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 452",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 452,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "This magic comes from the arcane tradition, which is built on logic and rationality. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to arcane magic.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "40b5d9c5e49dbe2aea5d7ecf38d950f3",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Mythic",
        "sources": [
          {
            "link": {
              "alt": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
              "aonid": 232,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "War of Immortals",
            "page": 69,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Options with this trait grant or utilize mythic power. Feats with the mythic trait can only be taken by mythic characters, who are typically characters with a mythic Calling.  \n  \n Monsters with the mythic trait have access to a pool of Mythic Points and are particularly strong for creatures of their level. Many mythic monsters are either resistant or entirely immune to attacks from non-mythic creatures and weapons.  \n  \n Spells with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to be cast, and items with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to use their activated abilities.  \n  \n Weapons with the mythic trait overcome the resistances and immunities of mythic monsters.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 164,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f7fe46b3a30bfb0e9bfbe655396afc22",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Wand",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 463,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A wand contains a single spell which you can cast once per day.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
